---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = new Date('2026-05-18T12:00:00+02:00');
---

<BaseLayout title="Now" description="A dated snapshot of what is alive across the four registers.">
  <main class="container">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
      <h1>What is alive right now.</h1>
      <p class="updated">last updated: <time datetime={updated.toISOString()}>18 May 2026</time></p>
    </header>

    <div class="snapshot">
      <section>
        <h2>Building</h2>
        <p>At Yubico, I am focused on developer-facing authentication infrastructure: SDKs, tooling, CI hardening, and the parts of security work that make strong defaults feel ordinary.</p>
        <p>In parallel, PAI is becoming my personal AI infrastructure: a local-first operating layer for memory, agent workflows, publishing, and the sovereignty stack around my own work.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Performing / Managing</h2>
        <p>Echological is the active music home: Hazayana Collective, Naomi Runa, Andreas Lång, Sophie von Matern, and Felicia Falck each need different kinds of scaffolding, care, and narrative precision.</p>
        <p>The next Echological work is about clearer artist surfaces, better booking materials, and a more deliberate bridge between live performance, community, and long-term careers.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Practicing</h2>
        <p>Meditation is in a maintenance season: ordinary sits, body awareness, and returning to Vipassana basics when the system gets noisy.</p>
        <p>Retreats, men's circles, and zen coaching continue as calibration: less performance, more contact with what is actually happening.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Reading / Listening</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><em>The Sovereign Individual</em>, James Dale Davidson and William Rees-Mogg</li>
          <li><em>Seeing That Frees</em>, Rob Burbea</li>
          <li><em>The Creative Act</em>, Rick Rubin</li>
          <li><em>Debt: The First 5,000 Years</em>, David Graeber</li>
          <li>Podcasts: Bankless, The Knowledge Project, and long-form conversations on AI tooling and contemplative practice.</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-md);"><a href="/library" style="color: var(--primary);">See the full library →</a></p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h2>Watching For</h2>
        <p>I am watching how personal AI changes the boundary between memory, agency, and dependency. The useful question is not "can the model do it?" but "does this make a human more sovereign or easier to capture?"</p>
        <p>Spring in Sweden has the same teaching in a simpler language: thaw first, growth second.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .container { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: var(--space-3xl) var(--space-lg); }
    .page-header { margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl); }
    .eyebrow { color: var(--gold); font-size: var(--type-small); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
    h1 { font-size: var(--type-h1); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
    .updated { color: var(--muted); font-size: var(--type-small); }
    .snapshot { display: grid; gap: var(--space-xl); }
    section { padding-bottom: var(--space-xl); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    h2 { font-size: var(--type-h3); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
    p, li { color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; }
    p + p { margin-top: var(--space-sm); }
    ul { padding-left: var(--space-lg); }
    li { margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
    @media (max-width: 768px) { h1 { font-size: var(--type-h2); } }
    .page-hero { margin: 0 0 var(--space-2xl); border-radius: var(--radius-md); overflow: hidden; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; background: var(--surface); }
    .page-hero img { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }

  </style>
</BaseLayout>
